FBIS4-67847 "jptnd010___94092" JPRS-TND-94-010 JPRS PROLIFERATION ISSUES 21 April 1994 INTERNATIONAL Pyongyang To Allow IAEA To Monitor Fuel Rod Exchange Pyongyang To Allow IAEA To Monitor Fuel Rod Exchange OW2104093994 Tokyo KYODO in English 0931 GMT 21 Apr 94 OW2104093994 Tokyo KYODO English BFN [Text] Seoul, April 21 KYODO -- North Korea will allow the International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) to allow monitoring the exchange of fuel rods at its 5,000-kilowatt nuclear reactor, the Korean Broadcasting System (KBS) said Thursday [21 April]. Pyongyang, in a telegram sent Wednesday to the UN nuclear watchdog, said it will exchange the fuel rods at the reactor soon and permit IAEA inspectors to monitor the process, according to KBS.
